
// This Hyperlambda snippet replaces all double quotes in the value of the [.description2] node with single quotes. It uses the [set-value] slot to update the node's value and the [strings.replace] slot to perform the string replacement operation. The first argument of [strings.replace] specifies the target string to look for, while the second argument specifies the replacement string.
set-value:x:@.description2
   strings.replace:x:@.description2
      .:"\""
      .:"'"
